{"author":{"id":"b78c39e7b13f90a5827abfba043255fe7a4ede1499df23f110fffe5abfa44adc"},"ops":[{"type":1,"timestamp":1769473321,"nonce":"WeeNXySyn22CPh81v30ClAbaVX0=","metadata":{"github-id":"I_kwDOQ241x87l-EF6","github-url":"https://github.com/rolker/ros2_agent_workspace/issues/51","origin":"github"},"title":"Protocol: Standardize Agent Signatures for Issues, PRs, and Comments","message":"## Problem\nWhile git commits are now attributed to specific agents (via `configure_git_identity.sh`), GitHub artifacts (Issues, Pull Requests, Comments) created via the API are still attributed solely to the PAT owner (`rolker`). This makes it hard to distinguish between human commands and agent actions in the GitHub UI.\n\n## Proposal: Content Signature Policy\nSince we cannot change the API-authenticated user (without a separate Machine User account), we will implement a **Content Signature** requirement.\n\n**Standard**:\nAll agents must append a signature footer to the body of any Issue, PR, or Comment they create.\n\n**Format**:\n```markdown\n\n---\n**🤖 Authored-By**: `\u003cAgent Name\u003e`\n```\n\n**Example**:\n```markdown\n...\nThis PR fixes the temporary file issue.\n\n---\n**🤖 Authored-By**: `Gemini CLI Agent`\n```\n\n## Implementation Plan\n1.  **Update Strategy**: Modify `.agent/AI_IDENTITY_STRATEGY.md` to include this requirement for GitHub API interactions.\n2.  **New Rule**: Create `.agent/rules/common/ai-signature.md` defining the format and mandatory usage.\n3.  **Update Onboarding**: Add a brief mention in `AGENT_ONBOARDING.md` alongside the Git Identity step.\n\n## Benefits\n- **Visibility**: Clearly signals agent-generated content.\n- **Searchability**: Allows filtering by `\"Authored-By: \u003cAgent\u003e\"`.\n- **Auditability**: Helps trace which agent logic was responsible for a specific comment or issue.","files":null}]}